extendedInfo.description: This robust application lets you add and keep track of fuel and service costs for your automobile(s).  Separate entry modules are provided for fuel, including miles/kilometer per gallon/litre (MPG) (KPL) calculation, and service costs .  All entries can be viewed in a log which also allows access to the individual entries.  A summary report is provided for month-to-date, 6 months-to-date and year-to-date (paid version only) totals for costs and mileage.  Backup/Import and Track Business Miles feature included.  This app allows you to change to one of four currencies (dollar,euro,pound, and yen).**Free version limitations:* Allows entries for One Car* Month-to-Date and 6 Months-to-Date Totals Only* Ads supported* Backup/Import * Track Business Miles * Export to CSV * Graph for last 5 entries **Paid version Benefits* Entries for Multiple Cars* Includes Year-to-Date Totals on Report* No Ads* Backup/Import * Track Business Miles * Export to CSV 1 Year and All Records * Graph for last 10 entries Version 1.4 Features* Graphing

reviews.title: Great, Simple and Supported
reviews.comment: This app is very simple to use. The developer is quick to respond to questions, bug fixes and suggestions. Auto Log does what I need and is a simple way of replacing my paper logs for keeping up with mileage. There is still room to improve on the interface, but it is a great app that if you need to track mileage deserves supporting the developer\'s time to buy the full version.
reviews.author: Curt Ellis

reviews.title: Wonderful app, fantastically responsive developer
reviews.comment: I downloaded this app because I wanted to keep tract of my business miles. I liked it enough that I bought the full app.  I wrote the developer with some suggestions because it wasn\'t quite what I needed. He wrote back with the news that he had implemented my suggestions! I thought of some more, and he took care of those as well.   I recommend this to you. Not only is it an excellent app that does -far- more than mileage recording, it\'s developer likes his program and works to make it better.   -Michael
reviews.author: Michael Burkley

reviews.title: No MPG without :(
reviews.comment: This is a nice little app, but is missing key component:  Allowing me to enter my odometer information to calculate MPG. The mpg calculates only on the trip odometer, which I may not set all the time. Just enter the mileage and calculate from last entry.
reviews.author: Chris Freeman
